#!/bin/bash

curl -X POST "http://localhost:8000/generate-video" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "title": "Everyone on our street thinks my family is insane. Honestly… they are not wrong.",
    "type": "story",
    "story": "We live on what people in our city call the rich street. Not billionaire rich or anything, but definitely well off. Big houses, nice cars, that kind of vibe. My family alone is already a whole crowd. There are eight kids, three sisters and four brothers, and I am somewhere in the middle. Add my parents and grandparents and that is twelve people living in the same house. My grandfather made pretty good money when he was younger, my dad used to be a government minister, my grandma used to be a well known model, and my mom is a photographer who collaborates with different brands. Our house is big enough for all twelve of us with a huge backyard that connects to the backyard next door where my mom s brother lives with his six kids, my grandma on my mom s side, and recently his wife s sister moved in too. Between the two houses it is basically a small village of relatives. Everyone on our street knows us because we are always outside, kids running around, barbecues, family gatherings, loud conversations across the fence. The neighbors are friendly but they also think our family is kinda unhinged, in a good way. And honestly there are reasons for that. Let us start with my second oldest brother Eric. He got married and then on the literal day of the wedding he ran off with his bride s younger brother. Left the country with him. Completely cut off contact with our family and friends. And obviously that story could not stay secret because basically the whole neighborhood was at that wedding. Then there is my twin sister. We went to the same school, same class, and we looked so similar that people could barely tell us apart. Apparently she got so tired of hearing that, that one day she came home from dance practice looking like a completely different person. She took money from our dad s office without asking and spent it on a very dramatic makeover. She got hair extensions down to her knees, injected something into her cheekbones, got huge lip fillers, massive eyelash extensions, and shaved off her eyebrows. But the craziest part? She dyed the extensions bright neon lime green. Hair down to her back. Huge lips. Giant lashes. No eyebrows. When we saw her at dinner that night the entire house went silent and then exploded. Nobody even cared about the money she took, everyone was just staring at her face. Next comes my youngest brother. He is 14 now, puberty, hormones, teenage stupidity. Last week my grandma picked him up from soccer practice with two of our cousins. She stopped at a gas station for coffee and left the boys in the car for a few minutes. When she came back her entire car was covered in stickers of male and female genitals and they had written dirty phrases all over the windows. For context my grandma drives a purple Dodge Charger and my brother had been begging her all winter to let him drive it. She told him she would think about it. Well the second she saw what they did to her car that decision was made instantly. She had to drive home like that through our entire neighborhood and people are still laughing about it. And finally my favorite story from about three years ago. My uncle decided to appear in a commercial for toothpaste. He has veneers and thought his perfect white smile would be perfect for advertising whitening toothpaste. The photoshoot went great, he saw the preview pictures and loved them. Then about a week later a giant billboard with his face appeared right on our street. The problem? The designer added a weird warm filter to the photos which made his teeth look extremely yellow. Imagine a toothpaste ad about whitening teeth and the guy in the ad looks like he has not brushed in ten years. My uncle was so embarrassed that for two weeks he literally went jogging at night so nobody would see him outside. Eventually he managed to get the posters taken down but our family still laughs about it. So yeah, that is my weird family. But weird in a good way. I am part of this circus too, and despite all the chaos none of our stories have ever turned into anything criminal. Just a lot of ridiculous family legends."
  }'
